    "This embedded description of the task guided the computational response of the AI model toward less detailed plans.",
    "Additionally, the opening section of a lesson plan, called the Warm-up or Focus and Review, was labeled as the hook (Wiggins & McTighe, 2005).",
    "ChatGPT seemed to interpret this terminology as input that is teacher-centered and does not require student interaction, which resulted in lower scores for related portions of the lesson plan.",
    "As a consequence, once the lesson plan template was included as input beginning with P.3, the warmup/hook became almost formulaic.",
    "Though technically more specific, this decrease in score suggests that simply including a lesson plan template for context is not an effective strategy for increasing quality."
